# GitHub MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the GitHub MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# GITHUB_TOKEN - Your GitHub Personal Access Token
#   Generate a token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   Required scopes: repo, user, read:org (add more as needed for your use case)
#   This token is required for the GitHub MCP server to function
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: github-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/github:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
# GITHUB_API_URL - GitHub API URL (default: https://api.github.com)
#   For GitHub Enterprise, set this to your instance URL
#
# Examples:
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-github-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/github:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
# GITHUB_API_URL=https://github.example.com/api/v3
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
GITHUB_TOKEN=
# CONTAINER_NAME=github-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/github:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
# GITHUB_API_URL=https://api.github.com
